gw.api.database.upgrade

Class DeletePropertiesButNotColumnsIfSafeDatamodelChange

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.database.upgrade.DropColumnsAndDeletePropertiesIfSafeDatamodelChange
      • gw.api.database.upgrade.DeletePropertiesButNotColumnsIfSafeDatamodelChange

  • public class DeletePropertiesButNotColumnsIfSafeDatamodelChange
extends DropColumnsAndDeletePropertiesIfSafeDatamodelChange
    Checks that the given properties on the given entity are safe to drop, i.e. for each property: - it is not defined in the datamodel, and - it only contains the default value given If the property is defined in the datamodel, the property is not deleted. If the property is not defined in the datamodel and has only default values, the property is deleted. If the property is not defined in the datamodel and has non-default values, it will be left unchanged. This IDatamodelChange does not affect the database.
